				\begin{document}$$\varDelta ={\mu }_{\mathrm{REF}}-{\mu }_{\mathrm{ALT}}$$\end{document}Δ=μREF−μALTwhere, µREF, is the mean fragment size of reference allele fragments, µALT, is the mean size of variant allele fragments, and, Δ, is the test statistic. The null hypothesis was modeled using the data and the test statistic was calculated for 10,000 null datasets simulated using bootstrapping. Bootstrapped p values were estimated based on the fraction of the time that the simulated dataset gave a statistic equal to or greater than the observed statistic in the original dataset.
